Columns.Name: ComponentId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Component.

Columns.Name: ComponentLocationTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Component Location Type.

Columns.Name: PeriodStartTimestamp
Columns.Description: The period start timestamp for which an associated Component - Location relationship is effective.

Columns.Name: PeriodEndTimestamp
Columns.Description: The period end timestamp for which an associated Component - Location relationship is effective.

Columns.Name: LocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Location.

Columns.Name: GpsLatitude
Columns.Description:
The GPS latitude.

Wide Area Augmentation System GPS technology is accurate to 1-1.5 meters.

Columns.Name: GpsLongitude
Columns.Description:
The GPS longitude.

Wide Area Augmentation System GPS technology is accurate to 1-1.5 meters.

Columns.Name: ComponentLocationRelationshipTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Component Location Relationship Type.

Columns.Name: ComponentLocationInstallationTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that a component was installed at the associated location.

Columns.Name: LocationElevation
Columns.Description: The distance above/below ground level of the location where the component is located. If the location is above ground level this measurement will be positive, if the location is below ground level this measurement will be negative.

Columns.Name: LocationElevationUnitOfMeasureId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Unit Of Measure.

Columns.Name: ComponentLocationNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding a Component Location.
